# Rules excluded from install to ~/.claude/rules/ by rules/install.sh.
#
# These 7 common rules duplicate on-demand busdriver skills (litmus/code-review,
# tdd-workflow, the orchestrator pipeline, the live Agent-tool registry,
# coding-standards) or are stale (model-tier guidance), so they are kept OUT of
# always-loaded context (~3.7k tokens/session saved).
#
# The files REMAIN in the repo under rules/common/ — so their cross-references
# resolve, and sync-upstream keeps them current in the archive-free tree. Only
# the *install* step skips copying them to ~/.claude/rules/common/.
#
# To install one anyway: delete its line. To install everything (ignore this
# file): run `RULES_INSTALL_NO_EXCLUDE=1 ./install.sh ...`.
#
# One path per line, relative to rules/. '#' comments and blank lines ignored.
#
# NOTE: development-workflow.md is referenced by the kept git-workflow.md via a
# "see [development-workflow.md]" pointer; excluding it leaves that one cosmetic
# dead link in the installed git-workflow.md (its own content is complete — no
# functional impact). Remove the line below to keep that pointer live.
common/agents.md
common/code-review.md
common/coding-style.md
common/development-workflow.md
common/patterns.md
common/performance.md
common/testing.md
